struct User {
    username: String,
    email: String,
    sign_in_count: u64,
    active: bool,
}

slides.content:
To actually use your new `User` type, you create an **instance** inside your function.

```rust
let mut user1 = User {
    email: String::from("cool_guy@rust.com"),
    username: String::from("cool_guy_99"),
    active: true,
    sign_in_count: 1,
};
```
Notice you don't have to define fields in the exact order they were declared!

Because we made `user1` mutable using `let mut`, we can modify single fields using dot-notation!

```rust
user1.email = String::from("new_email@rust.com");
println!("Username is {}", user1.username);
```
